Patch Set 4: I would prefer that you didn't merge this

(6 inline comments)

This looks like a good start.  I have some comments/questions inline.

I would also like to see a dependent patch so that we can tell how this will be used.  Please do not get me wrong, I think it is very good that this is its own patch and should be reviewed separately, but at the same time I look forward to seeing the context of exactly how this will be used.

Patch Set 4: I would prefer that you didn't merge this

(2 inline comments)

Additional three comments:

1. I'm thinking a typical scenario:

The store_type_preference=swift, filesystem and exclude_unpreferred_location=True. Meanwhile, some of the images only have filesystem locations. Based on current design, seems an empty list will be returned. Please correct me if there is any misunderstanding.

2. I'd like to see a config sample.

3. Echoing John's comments, it would be nice if there is another patch to show how this code is leveraged.

Patch Set 7:

@flwang, as I mentioned in irc I have two comments on "exclude_unpreferred_location":

1. use case: admin can use this option to require glance disable backend storage(s) temporarily (or forever) for all images (or particular deployed nova/consumer node since this code will be shared between glance server and client both side in my plan).

2. I will make glance support those images which under 'active' status but have not available locations. Since "exclude_unpreferred_location" option can make some images can't return locations.
